li.p:
Explain why the factor

  e^{-2\alpha\pi^2t}

shrinks in time.

subsection.p:
The first chapter began with points, vectors, and displacements. At that stage, a vector was only an instruction:
\text{move this far in these directions.}
By the end of the book, the same geometric discipline has grown into a language for fields and laws.

